-- CNPC, Sinopec to Meet With Venezuela, Chavez Says
-- Steven Bodzin
-- 2009-04-07T19:57:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2009-04-07/cnpc-sinopec-to-meet-with-venezuela-chavez-says-update1-.html

          
          
             China  National Petroleum Corp. and
 China Petroleum & Chemical Corp. (600028) , known as Sinopec, will meet
tomorrow with a delegation led by Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez, the South American leader said today.  
 The Venezuelan state visit to China will also include
meetings to review the construction of a joint-venture refinery,
which is “already beginning,” Chavez said on state television.  
 Chavez is in Asia seeking financing for tens of billions of
dollars worth of oil and gas projects, including three in the
Orinoco Belt where the government is selecting partners. CNPC
and Sinopec are among the companies that are taking part in the
proposal and selection proposal, PDVSA said in December.  
 CNPC has a minority stake in the Petrocaracol joint
venture, which operates fields in  Venezuela , South America’s
biggest oil-producing country. The Chinese company’s services
division supplies oil and natural-gas drilling rigs. CNPC is
also certifying oil reserves in the Junin 4 area of the Orinoco
Belt.  
